# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers:
- Total blocks: 5 blocks
- Layers: 2 layers (base layer with orange cylinders, top layer with yellow blocks and blue cube)

## Spatial Relationships:
- Base layer: Two orange horizontal cylinders positioned parallel to each other
- Second layer: One yellow horizontal rectangular block placed across the two orange cylinders
- On top of the yellow rectangular block: A yellow half-cylinder (dome shape) at the right side
- On top of the yellow rectangular block: A blue cube at the left side

# Required Blocks from the Dictionary

Based on my analysis, I need the following blocks:
- Blue cube (index 1)
- Two orange horizontal cylinders (index 10)
- Yellow horizontal rectangular block (index 4)
- Yellow half-cylinder/dome (index 11)

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 10
    Step2: Move block with index 10
    Step3: Move block with index 4
    Step4: Move block with index 11
    Step5: Move block with index 1
}
```

This assembly sequence places the two orange cylinders as the base first, then adds the yellow rectangular block across them, followed by the yellow dome shape on the right side of the rectangle, and finally places the blue cube on the left side of the rectangle.
